This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes a new neural network architecture that outperforms existing models on multiple benchmark datasets. It may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category as it involves the design and optimization of a neural network architecture. Additionally, it could be classified under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category as it involves the development of a more efficient and effective neural network model. The paper also uses image datasets such as MNIST and pMNIST, which suggests it could belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves natural language processing tasks such as sentiment analysis, which could classify it under the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
